CUT ACROSS SHORTY forwardly placed in the early running, disputed the decent pace through the backstretch run, lost a bit of ground to JERRY JEFF WALKER along the second turn, re-rallied in upper stretch, confronted JERRY JEFF WALKER and dueled with that rival to mid-stretch, continued to battle to the final stages, was not able to get by a game JERRY JEFF WALKER in deep stretch and was outfinished by GROSS PROFIT at the finish, while holding for third in a good effort. LORD OF LIGHT allowed to settle, raced three wide along the first turn, slipped to the two path for the backstretch run, was steered three wide into the second turn, was roused four wide into the stretch, finished well inside of the furlong marker while on the left lead but could not reel in the leaders in the final stages. DE LA LUNA unhurried through decent early fractions, saved ground through the backstretch run, came two wide into the second turn, was roused three wide into the stretch, improved position at the furlong marker and offered a mild late rally in the late stages. NEVER HAD I EVER tracked the decent early pace, saved all of the ground through the backstretch run, dropped back along the second turn and tired in the stretch.
